==Assyrian Neo-Aramaic==
{{phrasebook|aii}}

===Etymology 1===
{{aii-root|ܫ ܠ ܡ}}
Common {{cog|sem-nwe}}, from {{inh|aii|arc|שְׁלָמָא|tr=šəlāmā}}; compare {{cog|he|שָׁלוֹם|tr=shalóm}}, {{cog|phn|𐤔𐤋𐤌}}, {{cog|ar|سَلَام}} and {{cog|uga|𐎌𐎍𐎎|ts=šalāmu}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|aii|[ˈʃlɑːmɑː]|a=Standard}}
* {{IPA|aii|[ˈʃlaːma]|a=Nineveh Plains}}

====Interjection====
{{aii-interj|ܫܠܵܡܵܐ}}

# {{q|conventional greeting}} [[hello]], [[hi]]
#: {{syn|aii|ܫܠܵܡܵܐ ܥܲܠܘܼܟ݂|q1=sometimes formal; to a man|ܫܠܵܡܵܐ ܥܲܠܵܟ݂ܝ|q2=sometimes formal; to a woman|ܫܠܵܡܵܐ ܥܲܠܵܘܟ݂ܘܿܢ|q3=sometimes formal; to a group}}

====Noun====
{{aii-noun|ܫܠܵܡܵܐ|m|pl=ܫܠܵܡܹ̈ܐ}}

# {{lb|aii|uncountable}} [[peace]], [[harmony]] {{gloss|freedom from disturbance}}
#: {{syn|aii|ܫܲܝܢܵܐ}}
# {{lb|aii|uncountable}} [[well-being]], [[welfare]]
# {{lb|aii|countable}} [[greeting]], [[salutation]], [[salute]]
# {{lb|aii|Christianity}} [[pax]], [[kiss of peace]]
#: {{uxa|aii|ܒܥܹܕܬܵܐ ܟܹܐ ܝܵܗ݇ܒ݂ܲܚ '''ܫܠܵܡܵܐ''' ܚܲܕ݇ ܠܚܲܕ݇ ܒܐܝܼ̈ܕ݂ܵܬ݂ܲܢ|t=In church, we give the '''pax''' (greet) each other with our hands.}}
# {{lb|aii|ecclesiastical}} invocation of peace, ''[[pax vobiscum]]''

=====Inflection=====
{{aii-infl-noun/m|ܫܠܵܡ}}

=====Derived terms=====
* {{l|aii|ܝܵܗ݇ܒ݂ܹܠ ܫܠܵܡܹ̈ܐ|t=to greet}}
* {{l|aii|ܫܵܐܹܠ ܒܲܫܠܵܡܵܐ|t=to ask [[how]] one [[be|is]], to ask about the [[health]] of}}

===Etymology 2===
{{number box|aii|1}}
Compare {{cog|he|שָׁלֵם|tr=shalém}} and {{cog|ar|سَالِم}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|aii|[ʃal.mɑː]|a=Standard}}

====Adjective====
{{aii-adjective|ܫܲܠܡܵܐ|f=ܫܲܠܡܬ݂ܵܐ|pl=ܫܲܠܡܹ̈ܐ}}

# [[whole]], [[perfect]], [[complete]]
# [[peaceful]], [[harmonious]]
# [[healthy]], [[safe]]
# {{lb|aii|mathematics}} [[whole]], [[integral]]
# {{lb|aii|grammar}} [[strong]] [[plural]]

=====Derived terms=====
{{col|aii|ܓܲܒ݂ܪܵܐ ܫܲܠܡܵܐ<t:[[adult]]>
|ܫܲܠܡܵܐܝܼܬ݂<t:[[entirely]], [[fully]]>
|ܫܲܠܡܘܼܬ݂ܵܐ<t:[[completion]]>
|ܒܲܪ ܫܲܠܡܘܼܬ݂ܵܐ<t:agreeable person>
|ܫܲܠܡܘܼܬ݂ܵܢܵܝܵܐ<t:[[consensual]]>}}

