==Classical Syriac==

===Alternative forms===
* Aramaic: {{l|arc|sc=Hebr|שְׁלָמָא}}

===Etymology 1===
[[File:ACMA 1333 Samian decree 2.JPG|thumb|[[Hera]] and [[Athena]] handshaking, late 5th century BC, Acropolis Museum, Athens]]
{{syc-rootbox|ܫ ܠ ܡ}}
Compare {{cog|phn|𐤔𐤋𐤌}}, {{cog|he|שָׁלוֹם|tr=šālōm}}, {{cog|uga|𐎌𐎍𐎎|ts=šalāmu}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|syc|[ʃ(ə.)ˈlɑ.mɑ]|a=Classical Edessan}}
* {{IPA|syc|[ˈʃlɑ.mɑ]|a=Eastern Syriac}}
* {{IPA|syc|[ˈʃlo.mo]|a=Western Syriac}}

====Interjection====
{{head|syc|interjection|head1=ܫܠܵܡܵܐ|head2=ܫܠܳܡܳܐ|tr=šəlāmā|tr2=šlomo}}

# A greeting; equivalent to [[hello]].

====Noun====
{{head|syc|noun|head1=ܫܠܵܡܵܐ|head2=ܫܠܳܡܳܐ|tr=šəlāmā|tr2=šlomo}}

# [[peace]], [[wholeness]], [[perfection]], [[completeness]]
#: [[Peshitta]], [[Colossians|Epistle to the Colossians]] 1:2:
#* {{quote|syc|'''ܫܠܡܐ '''ܥܡܟܘܢ ܘܛܝܒܘܬܐ ܡܢ ܐܠܗܐ ܐܒܘܢ|tr='''šəlāmā''' ʿamḵōn wə-ṭaybūṯā men ʾălāhā ʾăḇūn|'''Peace''' be with you and grace from God our Father}}
# [[health]], [[welfare]], [[safety]], [[prosperity]]
# [[greeting]], [[salutation]], [[salute]]
# {{lb|syc|Christianity}} [[pax]], [[kiss of peace]]
# {{lb|syc|ecclesiastical}} invocation of peace, ''[[pax vobiscum]]''

=====Inflection=====
{{syc-decl-noun-m|ܫܠܡ}}

=====See also=====
* {{l|syc|ܫܝܢܐ|tr=šaynā}}
* {{l|syc|ܚܘܠܡܢܐ|tr=ḥūlmānā}}

===Etymology 2===
{{syc-rootbox|ܫ ܠ ܡ}}
Compare {{cog|he|שָׁלֵם|tr=šālēm}}. The sense of "strong plural" is a {{calque|syc|ar|سَالِم|nocap=1}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|syc|[ˈʃal.mɑ]|a=Classical Edessan}}
* {{IPA|syc|[ˈʃal.mɑ]|a=Eastern Syriac}}
* {{IPA|syc|[ˈʃɑl.mo]|a=Western Syriac}}

====Adjective====
{{syc-adj|pl=ܫܠܡܐ|tr=šalmā|pltr=šalmē|f=ܫܠܡܬܐ|ftr=šəlamṯā}}

# [[peaceful]], [[harmonious]]
# [[whole]], [[perfect]], [[unblemished]], [[complete]], [[entire]], [[full]], [[achieved]]
# [[healthy]], [[well]], [[safe]], [[sound]], [[prosperous]]
# [[common]], [[accessible]]

=====Inflection=====
{{syc-infl-adj|ܫܠܡ}}

====Noun====
{{syc-noun|tr=šalmā|m|ܫܠܡܐ|pltr=šalmē}}

# {{lb|syc|grammar}} [[strong]] [[plural]] (as opposed to a [[broken]] plural)
# [[holocaust]], [[sacrifice]], [[burnt offering]]

=====Inflection=====
{{syc-decl-noun-m|ܫܠܡ}}

===Etymology 3===

====Pronunciation 1====
* {{IPA|syc|[ˈʃɑl.mɑ]|a=Classical Edessan}}
* {{IPA|syc|[ˈʃɑl.mɑ]|a=Eastern Syriac}}
